Library Management System

Classes:

*Book: Represents a book with attributes like title, author, publication year, etc.
*Library: Manages a collection of books.
*Main: Contains the main method to run the application.

Features:

1) Add Books to Library: Create a method to add books to the library.
2) Display Books: Show all the books in the library.
3) Search Books by Author/Title: Use lambda functions to filter books by author or title.
4) Update Book Information: Allow updating book details.
5) Remove Books: Remove books from the library.
6) Count Books: Count the total number of books available.
7) Additional Functionality: You can add additional features like sorting books by title or author using lambda functions.